chatgpt_solution:
We begin our solution by expressing the given line in slope-intercept form. We have $3x - 2y = 6$, or $2y = 3x - 6$, which means $y = \frac32 x - 3$.  Since we want the line perpendicular to this one, we want its slope to be the negative reciprocal of $\frac32$.  The negative reciprocal is $-\frac{2}{3}$, so our line has slope $-\frac23$.  This line also has a $y$-intercept of 2, so the line in slope-intercept form is $y = -\frac23 x + 2$.  The $x$-intercept is the point $(x,0)$ at which this line intersects the $x$-axis.  Substituting 0 for $y$ in the equation $y = -\frac23 x + 2$ gives us $0 = -\frac23 x+2$.  Solving for $x$ gives us $x = \boxed{3}$. [asy]
size(200,200);
real ticklen=3;
real tickspace=2;

real ticklength=0.1cm;

real axisarrowsize=0.14cm;

pen axispen=black+1.3bp;
pen tickpen=black+1.3bp;
pen arrowpen=black+1.3bp;

real vectorarrowsize=0.2cm;

pen vectorpen=black+1bp;
pen dotpen=dotfactor*dotfactor+linewidth(4bp);

real xaxismin=-2;
real xaxismax=6.5;
real yaxismin=-6;
real yaxismax=4.5;

real x=3;
real slope=-2/3;
real yintercept=2;
real y=slope*x+yintercept;


pair A=(xaxismin,0),B=(xaxismax,0),C=(0,yaxismin),D=(0,yaxismax);
draw(A--B,axispen,EndArrow(size=axisarrowsize));
draw(C--D,axispen,EndArrow(size=axisarrowsize));
label("$x$",(B.x,-axisarrowsize),S);
label("$y$",(D.y,-axisarrowsize),E);

real xtickbegin=xaxismin+Ceiling(tickspace/xaxismin)*tickspace;
for(real i=xtickbegin;i<=xaxismax;i+=tickspace) { draw((i,-ticklength)--(i,ticklength),tickpen); label(format("$%.1f$",i),(i,-2*ticklength),2*S); }
real ytickbegin=yaxismin+Ceiling(tickspace/yaxismin)*ticklength;
for(real i=ytickbegin;i<=yaxismax;i+=tickspace) { draw((-ticklength,i)--(ticklength,i),tickpen); label(format("$%.1f$",i),(-2*ticklength,i),2*W); }

draw(graph(slope*x+yintercept,A,B),vectorpen,EndArrow(size=vectorarrowsize));

dot((x,0),dotpen);

label("$3$",(x,0),1.5*SE);
[/asy]
